ENTRY            A1461   20260317   20260508   20260508       A133
SUBENT        A1461001   20260317   20260508   20260508       A133
BIB                 12         40
TITLE      The 7Li(p,gamma)8Be* reaction and single-particle
           levels in 8Be
AUTHOR     (J.B.Marion,M.Wilson)
REFERENCE  (J,NP,77,129,1966)
           (T,WILSON,1965) tables; experim. description
           (J,PL,14,313,1965) Preliminary accounts of this
           experiment and
           (J,PL,14,315,1965) the result's interpretation
INSTITUTE  (1USAMRY)
FACILITY   (VDG,1USAMRY)
SAMPLE     The targets consisted of a thin film of LiF deposited
           on 0.75 inch diam. x 0.20 inch thick tantalum disks
           by vacuum evaporation.
METHOD     (BCINT)
DETECTOR   (MAGSP,SOLST,PLATE) The alpha-particles were momentum
           analyzed in a 180. degr. double-focusing magnetic
           spectrometer of 50 cm radius. The plates were made of
           thin glass, 8 inches by 2 inches, supporting a
           50 micron thick K-1 or K-2 emulsion composition.
           (SOLST)  A solid-state detector was used for some
           confirmatory measurements as well as for a
           determination of the alpha0 excitation function for
           the purpose of normalizing the emulsion data.
            An independent measurement of the alpha0 excitation
           curve was made with another solid state detector (but
           not used in conjunction with the magnetic spectrometer)
EN-SEC     (E-LVL,4-BE-8)
COMMENT    From the article: The 8Be levels in question (16.62
           and 16.92 MeV) can particle-decay only by the breakup
           into two alpha particles; each level has an
           alpha-particle width of approximately 0.1 MeV.
ADD-RES    A final confirmation of the occurrence of the
           7Li(p,gamma)8Be*(alpha)4He reaction was obtained by
           observing coincidences between the capture gamma
           radiation and the breakup particles.
HISTORY    (19800907C) Compilation produced by RFNC-VNIIEF Sarov
           (19990321U)CNPD: corrected 4-dig. year and lower cases.
           (20200319A) SD: Corrections in all Subents. Digitized
           data were changed on tabulated from thesis. BIB updated
           (20260317A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              40
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           43
SUBENT        A1461002   20260317   20260508   20260508       A133
BIB                  6         10
REACTION   (3-LI-7(P,A)2-HE-4,ISP,DA)
